cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the efficiency and accuracy of Deep Neural Network (DNN) inference at runtime, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of dynamic feedback and power-limit settings, which are related to system design and optimization, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.SD (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
